{{Lunisolar September}} '''September 23''' is the 23rd day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} .
== Events == * {{ill|Wadō|ja|和銅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|712|ja|712|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 27|ja|10月27日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – The region of Echigo split the Dewa district off into a separate Dewa Province. * {{ill|Teiji|ja|貞治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year/{{ill|Shōhei|ja|正平|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 17th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1362|ja|1362|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 11|ja|10月11日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – The Northern Court changed its era name from {{ill|Kang'an|ja|康安|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Teiji|ja|貞治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . * {{ill|Kansei|ja|Kansei|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1800|ja|1800|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – Inō Tadataka completed his survey of Ezo and the Ōshū Kaidō, then returned to Edo and presented his preliminary map to the shogunate. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1857|ja|1857|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – U.S. Consul {{ill|Townsend Harris|ja|ハリス|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} visited Edo Castle and met with Tokugawa Iesada. == Births == * {{ill|Genroku|ja|Genroku|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 15th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1702|ja|1702|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 24|ja|10月24日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Yokoi Yayuu|ja|横井也有|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a haiku poet († {{ill|1783|ja|1783|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Hōreki|ja|Hōreki|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1760|ja|1760|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 30|ja|11月30日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Kawaoka Seishū|ja|華岡青洲|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a physician and pioneer of anesthesia († {{ill|1835|ja|1835|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Bunka (era)|ja|文化 (元号)|lt=Bunka|lt_ja=文化|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 14th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1817|ja|1817|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 1|ja|12月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Ono Yūgorō|ja|小野友五郎|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a mathematician († {{ill|1898|ja|1898|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1849|ja|1849|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Saionji Kinmochi|ja|西園寺公望|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , who served as Prime Minister on two occasions and as genrō († {{ill|1940|ja|1940|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1871|ja|1871|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 5|ja|12月5日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Doi Bansui|ja|土井晩翠|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a poet († {{ill|1952|ja|1952|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tenshōjingo|ja|Tenpyō神護|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|765|ja|765|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 10|ja|11月10日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – Emperor {{ill|Junnin|ja|淳仁天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , the 47th emperor. * {{ill|Kanbun|ja|寛文|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 9th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1669|ja|1669|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 16|ja|11月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Shakusha In|ja|シャクシャイン|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , the Ainu chief. * {{ill|Taihei Kōkoku|ja|太平興国|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|976|ja|976|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 14|ja|11月14日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – Emperor {{ill|Zhao Kuangyin|ja|趙匡胤|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Taizu), the first emperor of the Northern Song (* {{ill|927|ja|927|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Daiji (Japan)|ja|大治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1127|ja|1127|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 25|ja|11月25日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshimitsu|ja|源義光|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a military commander and younger brother of {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshiie|ja|源義家|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (* {{ill|1045|ja|1045|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Eikyō|ja|永享|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1433|ja|1433|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 1|ja|12月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – Emperor {{ill|Go-Komatsu|ja|後小松天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , the 100th emperor of the Northern Court (* {{ill|1377|ja|1377|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1856|ja|1856|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 17|ja|11月17日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Ninomiya Sontoku|ja|二宮尊徳|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , an agrarian reformer (* {{ill|1787|ja|1787|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
