{{Lunisolar September}} '''September 23''' is the 23rd day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} .
== Events == * {{ill|Wadō|ja|和銅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|712|ja|712|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 27|ja|10月27日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – The region of Echigo split the Dewa district off into a separate Dewa Province. * {{ill|Teiji|ja|貞治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year/{{ill|Shōhei|ja|正平|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 17th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1362|ja|1362|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 11|ja|10月11日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – The Northern Court changed its era name from {{ill|Kang'an|ja|康安|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Teiji|ja|貞治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . * {{ill|Kansei|ja|Kansei|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1800|ja|1800|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – Inō Tadataka completed his survey of Ezo and the Ōshū Kaidō, then returned to Edo and presented his preliminary map to the shogunate. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1857|ja|1857|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – U.S. Consul {{ill|Townsend Harris|ja|ハリス|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} visited Edo Castle and met with Tokugawa Iesada. == Births == * {{ill|Genroku|ja|Genroku|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 15th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1702|ja|1702|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 24|ja|10月24日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Yokoi Yayuu|ja|横井也有|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a haiku poet († {{ill|1783|ja|1783|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Hōreki|ja|Hōreki|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1760|ja|1760|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 30|ja|11月30日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Kawaoka Seishū|ja|華岡青洲|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a physician and pioneer of anesthesia († {{ill|1835|ja|1835|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Bunka (era)|ja|文化 (元号)|lt=Bunka|lt_ja=文化|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 14th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1817|ja|1817|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 1|ja|12月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Ono Yūgorō|ja|小野友五郎|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a mathematician († {{ill|1898|ja|1898|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1849|ja|1849|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Saionji Kinmochi|ja|西園寺公望|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , who served as Prime Minister on two occasions and as genrō († {{ill|1940|ja|1940|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1871|ja|1871|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 5|ja|12月5日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Doi Bansui|ja|土井晩翠|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a poet († {{ill|1952|ja|1952|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
