== Events == * [[:en:Wadō (era)|Wadō]] 5th year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|712|ja|712|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/712|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 700}} [[:en:October 27|October 27]] ） – The region of Echigo split the Dewa district off into a separate Dewa Province. * [[:en:Jōji|Teiji]] 1st year/[[:en:Zhengping|Shōhei]] 17th year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1362|1362]] [[:en:October 11|October 11]] ） – The Northern Court changed its era name from [[:en:Kōan (Muromachi period)|Kang'an]] to [[:en:Jōji|Teiji]] . * {{ill|Kansei|ja|Kansei|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kansei|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 12nd year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1800|ja|1800|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1800|qq=}} [[:en:December 7|December 7]] ） – Inō Tadataka completed his survey of Ezo and the Ōshū Kaidō, then returned to Edo and presented his preliminary map to the shogunate. * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 4th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1857|ja|1857|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1857|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} [[:en:December 7|December 7]] ） – U.S. Consul [[:en:Harris|Townsend Harris]] visited Edo Castle and met with Tokugawa Iesada. == Births == * {{ill|Genroku|ja|Genroku|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Genroku|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 15th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1702|1702]] [[:en:October 24|October 24]] ） – [[:en:Yokoi Yayū|Yokoi Yayuu]] , a haiku poet († {{ill|1783|ja|1783|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1783|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ). * [[:en:Hōreki|Hōreki]] 10th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1760|ja|1760|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1760|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1000}} [[:en:November 30|November 30]] ） – [[:en:Hanaoka Seishū|Kawaoka Seishū]] , a physician and pioneer of anesthesia († {{ill|1835|ja|1835|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1835|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ). * [[:en:Bunka|Bunka]] 14th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1817|ja|1817|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1817|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} [[:en:December 1|December 1]] ） – {{ill|Ono Yūgorō|ja|小野友五郎|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ono Yūgorō|qq=}} , a mathematician († {{ill|1898|ja|1898|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1898|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ). * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 2nd year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1849|ja|1849|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1849|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1000}} [[:en:December 7|December 7]] ） – [[:en:Saionji Kinmochi|Saionji Kinmochi]] , who served as Prime Minister on two occasions and as genrō († {{ill|1940|ja|1940|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1940|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 4th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1871|ja|1871|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1871|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1000}} [[:en:December 5|December 5]] ） – {{ill|Doi Bansui|ja|土井晩翠|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Doi Bansui|qq=}} , a poet († {{ill|1952|ja|1952|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1952|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tenshōjingo|ja|Tenpyō神護|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshōjingo|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 1st year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|765|ja|765|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/765|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} [[:en:November 10|November 10]] ） – Emperor [[:en:Emperor Junnin|Junnin]] , the 47th emperor. * [[:en:Kanbun (era)|Kanbun]] 9th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1669|1669]] [[:en:November 16|November 16]] ） – {{ill|Shakusha In|ja|シャクシャイン|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakusha In|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} , the Ainu chief. * {{ill|Taihei Kōkoku|ja|太平興国|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taihei Kōkoku|qq=}} 1st year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|976|ja|976|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/976|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 900}} [[:en:November 14|November 14]] ） – Emperor [[:en:Emperor Taizu of Song|Zhao Kuangyin]] (Taizu), the first emperor of the Northern Song (* {{ill|927|ja|927|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/927|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ). * {{ill|Daiji (Japan)|ja|大治|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daiji (Japan)|qq=}} 2nd year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1127|1127]] [[:en:November 25|November 25]] ） – [[:en:Minamoto no Yoshimitsu|Minamoto no Yoshimitsu]] , a military commander and younger brother of [[:en:Minamoto no Yoshiie|Minamoto no Yoshiie]] (* [[:en:1045|1045]] ). * [[:en:Eikyō|Eikyō]] 5th year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1433|1433]] [[:en:December 1|December 1]] ） – Emperor [[:en:Emperor Go-Komatsu|Go-Komatsu]] , the 100th emperor of the Northern Court (* [[:en:1377|1377]] ). * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 3rd year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1856|ja|1856|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1856|qq=}} [[:en:November 17|November 17]] ） – [[:en:Ninomiya Sontoku|Ninomiya Sontoku]] , an agrarian reformer (* {{ill|1787|ja|1787|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1787|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ).
